info.ephyra.questionanalysis.atype.classifier
Class RuleElement

java.lang.Object
  info.ephyra.questionanalysis.atype.classifier.RuleElement

public class RuleElement
extends java.lang.Object

An element in a rule used for rule-based classification of answer type. Each RuleElement corresponds to a feature with a set of values with which to match a given Instance.

Method Detail

matches

public java.lang.String matches(edu.cmu.minorthird.classify.Instance instance)
Tells whether a given Instance has a feature that matches this RuleElement. by returning the matching value upon a successful match or null if this RuleElement does not match the Instance. When one of this RuleElement's values contains the substring "->", the portion of the value before the "->" is used for matching against the input Instance, while the portion of the value after the "->" is used as the matching value;

Parameters:
instance - the Instance to consider
Returns:
whether a given Instance has a feature that matches this RuleElement
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if this RuleElement has not been compiled yet
